  "text": "Construction of trpE fusions. cDNA clones of the PR159 strain of dengue virus type 2 were used for all plasmid constructions [CITATION_1] . All plasmids were constructed by using standard recombinant DNA techniques and were purified on CsCl density gradients [CITATION_2] per pul were programmed with in vitro-transcribed RNA at a concentration of 5 to 10,ug/ml. All translations were carried out at 30°C for 90 min unless otherwise noted.",
